    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1825_04_23_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#St-Stephens-Green_IE"/>St Stephens Green N.
                        <date when="1825-12-23">Dec. 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1825</date></dateline>
                    <salute>
                        Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    I am afraid that you must think<lb/>
                    me very negligent with regard to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockJ3">Johnny</persName>. <hi rend="underline">Breeks.</hi><lb/>
                    The man by whom I intended sending them was<lb/>
                    going, just a going, for so long a time that my<lb/>
                    patience at last went, and I sent of the above<lb/>
                    mentioned <unclear>Breeks per Van</unclear>. As the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#LockX1">Lockharts</persName> left<lb/>
                    <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edinburgh_STK"><choice><orig>Edin<hi rend="superscript">gh</hi></orig><reg>Edinburgh</reg></choice></placeName> for town much sooner than we expected. I have<lb/>
                    no doubt but that the box arrived three days after they<lb/>
                    started and will follow them with their heavy<lb/>
                    luggage. When I write home I shall make all<lb/>
                    due enquiry after it - and let you know the result.<lb/>
                    I regret very much not seeing <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Edgeworth</persName> whilst<lb/>
                    she was in town but for the last four weeks<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_23131_1825_04_23_page02.jpg"/>
                    I have been confined to my rooms and even<lb/>
                    yesterday could not avail myself of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WallE1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> <choice><orig>Wallers</orig><reg>Waller's</reg></choice></persName><lb/>
                    kind invitation for <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotJ1">Jane</persName> and I. so much for<lb/>
                    driving tandem. The <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> gaieties have not<lb/>
                    begun, there is some affair at the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin-Castle_IE">Castle</placeName> on<lb/>
                    Tuesday but I do not think I shall be well even<lb/>
                    to go. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotJ1">Jane</persName> joins me in best remembrance<lb/>
                    to all of <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"><choice><orig>Edgeworths Town</orig><reg>Edgeworthstown</reg></choice></placeName> and with all<lb/>
                    <choice><orig>comp<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi></orig><reg>compliments</reg></choice> of the season<lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <unclear>believe me yours</unclear><lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW4">Walter Scott</persName><lb/>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <note place="bottom"><persName ref="./Personography.xml#ScotW4"><hi rend="underline"><choice><orig>Capt</orig><reg>Captain</reg></choice></hi> Walter Scott</persName><lb/></note>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
             </div>
